⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Dennis Vinyard
node AHX · AHX · ⟦Dennis Vinyard:AHX:4042a2⟧

WHO   — Dennis Vinyard — the seed at the table
WHAT  — The root cause: hate as inheritance, taught in an ordinary kitchen and outliving the man who taught it.
WHERE — AHX · American History X (1998)  Framework inputs: American History X (1998, dir. Tony Kaye, New Line); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film locates the origin of the hate not in monsters but in a father's offhand prejudice.
HOW   — By dismissing a Black author's book and 'affirmative blacktion' over dinner — and dying before he could see what he'd sown.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I said it like it was nothing, over dinner, to my boy. It was the most important thing I ever taught him, and the worst.

